-- South Africa Loses 4.3 Million Pools of Water a Month: Times
-- B y   J a c o   V i s s e r
-- 2013-06-23T09:51:56Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-06-23/south-africa-loses-4-3-million-pools-of-water-a-month-times.html
Africa’s largest economy loses 4.3
million swimming pools worth of water a month through theft and
leaks, or about 417 billion gallons annually, the Sunday Times
said, citing a study by the Water Research Commission.  The annual loss equals a third of the capacity of country’s
largest dam, Gariep, the Johannesburg-based newspaper said. The
water loss equates to 7.2 billion rand ($709 million) a year,
the Times said, citing the commission’s study  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jaco Visser in Johannesburg at 
